goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving a good overview of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary by variety?
goals.visualization: grouped bar chart of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A grouped bar chart can show the yield of each variety side-by-side, making it easy to compare the performance of different varieties.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield at each site?
goals.rationale: A histogram can show the frequency distribution of yield at each site, giving an idea of the shape and spread of the distribution.

goals.question: How does the yield vary by year?
goals.visualization: line chart of yield by year
goals.rationale: A line chart can show the trend of yield over time, making it easy to see if there are any patterns or changes in yield from year to year.

goals.question: Is there a relationship between yield and location?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of yield by location
goals.rationale: A scatter plot can show the relationship between yield and location, making it easy to see if there are any patterns or correlations between the two variables.

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    data.boxplot(column='yield', ax=ax)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?", wrap=True)
    
    median_yield = data['yield'].median()
    plt.axhline(y=median_yield, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Yield: {median_yield:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    sites = data['site'].unique()
    for site in sites:
        site_data = data[data['site'] == site]['yield']
        plt.hist(site_data, alpha=0.5, label=site)
    
    plt.xlabel('Yield')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Site')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield at each site?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('year')['yield'].mean()
    plt.plot(data_grouped.index, data_grouped.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("How does the yield vary by year?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
